-sunak-announced-snap-election-on-july-4-787157%5C%22%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%20as%20he%20last%20week%20called%20for%20an%20early%20general%20election.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-pm-rishi-sunak-on-why-he-called-for-snap-elections-5723956%5C%22%3Eheavy%20rain%20drenched%20Sunak%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20new%20Labour%20anthem%2C%20%3Cem%3EThings%20Can%20Only%20Get%20Better%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20blared%20from%20a%20nearby%20loudspeaker%2C%20the%20Tory%20leader%20vowed%20to%20%26quot%3Bfight%20for%20every%20vote%26quot%3B.%20The%20announcement%20took%20many%20even%20in%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20rank%20and%20file%20by%20surprise.%20But%20things%20had%20only%20been%20going%20from%20bad%20to%20worse%20for%20the%20Tories%2C%20and%20thus%2C%20Sunak's%20move%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20salvage%20whatever%20he%20could%20of%20the%20Conservatives%20from%20the%20rubble%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Economy%20Pitch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Sunak%2C%20the%20only%20hope%20lies%20in%20framing%20the%20electoral%20contest%20around%20the%20theme%20of%20economic%20recovery%2C%20given%20that%20inflation%20has%20fallen%20and%20the%20UK%20economy%20grew%20by%200.6%25%20between%20January%20and%20March%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20for%20two%20years.%20He%20has%20decided%20to%20bet%20on%20his%20ability%20to%20convince%20the%20British%20voters%20that%20he%20is%20the%20best-placed%20candidate%20to%20deliver%20an%20economic%20revival.%20The%20economy%20is%20thus%20set%20to%20become%20a%20key%20talking%20point%20in%20the%20upcoming%20general%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20this%20move%20helps%20or%20hurts%20Sunak%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20the%20Labour%20Party%20is%20likely%20to%20keep%20sharpening%20its%20focus%20on%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living.%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%20underlined%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Btime%20for%20change%26quot%3B%2C%20blaming%20Tory%20%26quot%3Bchaos%26quot%3B%20for%20damaging%20the%20economy%20and%20making%20a%20case%20that%20a%20vote%20for%20his%20party%20was%20a%20chance%20to%20bring%20political%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fuk-pm-rishi-sunak-the-conservatives-up-the-creek-without-a-paddle-5373007%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Opinion%3A%20Rishi%20Sunak%20-%20Up%20The%20Creek%20Without%20A%20Paddle%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20among%20Sunak's%20closest%20advisors%20believed%20that%20while%20there%20certainly%20were%20green%20shoots%20of%20economic%20recovery%2C%20conditions%20might%20not%20improve%20significantly%20and%20that%20delaying%20the%20election%20could%20exacerbate%20a%20potential%20Conservative%20defeat%2C%20given%20the%20electorate's%20apparent%20desire%20for%20a%20timely%20say.%20Polls%20have%20consistently%20put%20Labour%20ahead%2C%20and%20this%20is%20a%20big%20moment%20for%20the%20opposition%20party%2C%20which%20has%20not%20won%20a%20UK%20general%20election%20since%202005.%20It%20looks%20like%20it%20is%20ready%20to%20assume%20governance%20as%20Starmer%20has%20been%20able%20to%20move%20Labour%20to%20the%20centre%2C%20a%20task%20no%20Labour%20leader%20was%20able%20to%20accomplish%20since%20the%20departure%20of%20Tony%20Blair%20in%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConservative%20Party's%20Internal%20Struggles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20has%20been%20at%20war%20with%20itself%2C%20a%20pale%20image%20of%20its%20past%20glory%20when%20it%20was%20deemed%20to%20be%20the%20natural%20party%20of%20governance.%20Despite%20Boris%20Johnson%20winning%20a%20massive%20victory%20in%202019%20for%20the%20Tories%2C%20his%20scandal-ridden%20premiership%20collapsed%20in%202022%2C%20leading%20to%20frequent%20leadership%20changes.%20The%20Conservative%20Party%20continued%20to%20experience%20a%20noticeable%20decline%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20marked%20by%20various%20challenges%20and%20shifts%20in%20the%20political%20landscape.%20It%20has%20faced%20internal%20divisions%2C%20particularly%20over%20Brexit%2C%20which%20have%20strained%20unity%20and%20led%20to%20significant%20leadership%20changes.%20Additionally%2C%20public%20dissatisfaction%20with%20handling%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20economic%20policies%20and%20social%20inequality%2C%20has%20eroded%20voter%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Frishi-sunak-sports-rs-79-000-backpack-during-campaign-visit-to-one-of-uks-poorest-areas-5773916%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Rishi%20Sunak%20Sports%C2%A0%E2%82%B9%C2%A079%2C000%20Backpack%20During%20Campaign%20Visit%20To%20One%20Of%20UK's%20Poorest%20Areas%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20an%20uphill%20road%20for%20Sunak%2C%20who%20tried%20his%20best%20to%20steady%20a%20wobbly%20Tory%20ship.%20But%20despite%20some%20of%20his%20noticeable%20achievements%2C%20he%20is%20not%20taken%20seriously%20as%20a%20leader.%20The%20Conservative%20rank%20and%20file%20don't%20see%20him%20as%20the%20person%20who%20can%20lead%20them%20to%20victory%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20they%20have%20been%20wary%20of%20replacing%20him%20for%20lack%20of%20options.%20For%20a%20party%20as%20ruthless%20as%20the%20Conservatives%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20changing%20its%20leadership%20for%20electoral%20success%2C%20this%20has%20been%20a%20difficult%20adjustment%2C%20and%20the%20strain%20is%20quite%20visible%20in%20its%20lack%20of%20self-confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELittle%20Changes%20For%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20UK's%20preoccupation%20with%20managing%20the%20externalities%20generated%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbrexit-becomes-reality-as-uk-leaves-european-unions-single-market-2346300%5C%22%3EBrexit%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20its%20relationship%20with%20India%20has%20continued%20to%20gain%20strength.%20The%20UK%20has%20increasingly%20recognised%20India%20as%20a%20pivotal%20player%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20its%20%26quot%3BIndo-Pacific%20tilt%26quot%3B%20strategy%2C%20under%20which%20aims%20to%20deepen%20ties%20with%20India%20as%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20regional%20engagement.%20India%20and%20the%20UK%20have%20bolstered%20their%20defence%20relationship%20through%20joint%20military%20exercises%2C%20defence%20dialogues%2C%20and%20collaboration%20on%20security%20issues.%20Cooperation%20in%20cybersecurity%20has%20been%20a%20priority%2C%20with%20both%20countries%20committing%20to%20enhance%20their%20capabilities%20and%20share%20best%20practices%20to%20tackle%20cyber%20threats.%20Both%20nations%20have%20worked%20closely%20on%20counterterrorism%20efforts%2C%20sharing%20intelligence%20and%20collaborating%20to%20combat%20global%20terrorism.%20Bilateral%20trade%20has%20grown%2C%20with%20significant%20investments%20flowing%20in%20both%20directions.%20The%20UK%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20top%20investors%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20in%20sectors%20such%20as%20services%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20infrastructure.%20Conversely%2C%20Indian%20companies%20have%20made%20substantial%20investments%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20IT%2C%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20and%20automotive%20sectors.%20Efforts%20to%20negotiate%20a%20comprehensive%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20have%20been%20a%20focal%20point%20of%20economic%20engagement.%20Educational%20ties%20have%20been%20strengthened%20through%20partnerships%20between%20universities%2C%20student%20exchange%20programmes%2C%20and%20collaborative%20research%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20new%20ambition%20in%20India's%20engagement%20with%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20what%20is%20heartening%20is%20that%20while%20the%20Conservatives%20