counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20related%20to%20hush-money%20payments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELegal%20experts%20said%20the%20defense%20made%20mistakes%20and%20that%20the%20prosecution%20told%20a%20better%20story.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20had%20previously%20said%20he%20would%20testify%20but%20ultimately%20didn't%2C%20which%20may%20have%20hurt%20his%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-reaction-hush-money-trial-guilty-verdict-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%3C%2Fa%3E%20historic%20conviction%20on%20Thursday%20may%20have%20been%20in%20part%20due%20to%20mistakes%20made%20by%20his%20defense%20team%2C%20including%20not%20having%20him%20take%20the%20stand%2C%20legal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20New%20York%20jury%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hush-money-trial-verdict-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econvicted%20Trump%20on%2034%20counts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20related%20to%20a%20hush-money%20payment%20made%20to%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels.%20The%20verdict%20made%20history%3A%20Trump%20is%20the%20only%20US%20president%20to%20also%20be%20a%20convicted%20felon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20case%20was%20significant%2C%20three%20legal%20experts%20told%20BI%20the%20verdict%20wasn't%20a%20major%20shock.%20Two%20said%20Trump's%20team%20made%20a%20number%20of%20mistakes%20during%20the%20trial%20that%20could%20have%20influenced%20the%20jury's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20say%20I'm%20surprised%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Reinert%2C%20a%20criminal%20law%20and%20constitutional%20law%20expert%20at%20the%20Cardozo%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it%20was%20a%20pretty%20simple%20case%20for%20the%20prosecution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bce02750-3b64-4efb-be00-f176bcb1edfc%5C%22%3EMistakes%20were%20made%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Anderson%2C%20a%20former%20prosecutor%20and%20current%20counsel%20at%20Early%20Sullivan%20Wright%20Gizer%20%26amp%3B%20McRae%20LLP%2C%20said%20the%20case%20could've%20gone%20either%20way%2C%20but%20that%20he%20thought%20the%20odds%20favored%20the%20prosecution%20going%20into%20deliberations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhoever%20has%20the%20best%20story%20wins%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20prosecution's%20story%20was%20very%20simply%3A%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20did%20something%20that%20on%20its%20face%2C%20could%20have%20been%20completely%20legal%2C%20but%20he%20did%20it%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20circumvent%20a%20federal%20election%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20he%20thought%20the%20defense's%20story%20just%20didn't%20work.%20For%20instance%2C%20they%20denied%20Trump%20ever%20had%20an%20affair%20with%20Daniels%20and%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20counter%20for%20it%2C%20even%20though%20many%20Americans%20already%20believe%20the%20alleged%20affair%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeama%20Rahmani%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20and%20president%20of%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%2C%20said%20the%20defense%20%26quot%3Boverpromised%20and%20underdelivered.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20opening%20statements%20made%20by%20Trump's%20lawyer%2C%20Todd%20Blanche%2C%20that%20Rahmani%20thought%20suggested%20an%20accountant%20would%20testify%20and%20serve%20as%20a%20fall%20guy.%20No%20such%20testimony%20was%20offered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20defense%20focused%20too%20much%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichael-cohen-reaction-trump-verdict-guilty-statement-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Cohen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Trump's%20former%20lawyer%2C%20but%20that%20he%20wasn't%20even%20the%20key%20witness.%20Instead%2C%20Rahmani%20said%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-feared-campaign-not-family-scandals-were-buried-pecker-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDavid%20Pecker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20former%20publisher%20of%20the%20National%20Enquirer%2C%20who%20was%20the%20key%20witness%20for%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20the%20one%20that%20directly%20tied%20Trump%20to%20the%20catch%20and%20kill%20scheme%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20said%20Cohen's%20testimony%20worked%20against%20Trump%2C%20despite%20the%20lawyer's%20potential%20credibility%20issues.%20He%20said%20often%20the%20most%20credible%20witnesses%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20own%20up%20to%20being%20liars%2C%20and%20that%20the%20defense%20just%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20rattle%20Cohen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20defense%20hadn't%20made%20these%20mistakes%2C%20it%20might%20not%20have%20made%20a%20difference%2C%20Rahmani%20said.%20Still%2C%20he%20thought%20they%20made%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%20for%20the%20jury%20to%20find%20Trump%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4d6d43e-6d1f-4e63-8d5f-ba48450e8fcb%5C%22%3ENot%20testifying%20may%20have%20hurt%20Trump%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20Trump%20would%20take%20the%20stand%20was%20a%20will-he-won't-he%20question%20for%20weeks%2C%20with%20the%20former%20president%20even%20saying%20he%20would%20testify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-manhattan-not-testify-criminal-hush-money-trial-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefense's%20case%20rested%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20Trump%20hadn't%20been%20called%20to%20the%20stand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDonald%20Trump%20never%20got%20up%20there%20and%20said%2C%20'Here's%20the%20reason%20I%20did%20this.'%20If%20you%20don't%20do%20that%2C%20all%20the%20jury%20is%20left%20with%20is%20the%20prosecution's%20version%20of%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20before%20resting%20their%20case%2C%20the%20defense%20told%20the%20judge%20they%20were%20still%20weighing%20having%20Trump%20testify.%20Some%20legal%20experts%20previous%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-unlikely-to-testify-in-hush-money-trial-reports-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestifying%20would%20not%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20for%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20concerns%20that%20he%20could%20end%20up%20committing%20perjury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Rahmani%20agreed%20that%20not%20having%20him%20speak%20up%20may%20have%20ultimately%20hurt%20his%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defense%20needed%20something%2C%20some%20sort%20of%20explanation%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahmani%20said%20of%20the%20falsified%20records.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20they%20would've%20been%20better%20off%20if%20either%20Trump%20or%20an%20accountant%20testified%2C%20'These%20were%20wrong%2C%20but%20it%20was%20an%20innocent%20mistake%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20claiming%20that%20a%20mistake%20was%20made%20with%20the%20records%2C%20Rahmani%20said%20the%20defense%20chose%20to%20%26quot%3Blie%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20closing%20statements%20and%20say%20there%20were%20no%20issues%20with%20the%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20they%20lost%20all%20credibility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eac7cf25-8936-4292-87fd-78761fb36991%5C%22%3EDon't%20expect%20to%20see%20Trump%20behind%20bars%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20sentencing%20is%20scheduled%20for%20July%2011.%20It's%20highly%20unlikely%20he%20will%20receive%20any%20jail%20time%2C%20the%20experts%20said.%20Instead%2C%20probation%20is%20most%20likely%2C%20or%20potentially%20home%20confinement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20Judge%20Merchan%20is%20going%20to%20send%20him%20to%20jail.%20It%20was%20clear%20when%20he%20violated%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-hit-gag-v