pointed%20to%20OpenAI's%20new%20safety%20committee%20and%20Altman's%20support%20for%20regulation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20the%20week%20of%20dueling%20op-eds%20from%20former%20and%20current%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20board%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20OpenAI%20board%20members%20Bret%20Taylor%20and%20Larry%20Summers%20issued%20a%20response%20to%20AI%20safety%20concerns%20on%20Thursday%2C%20stating%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20board%20is%20taking%20commensurate%20steps%20to%20ensure%20safety%20and%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20response%20comes%20a%20few%20days%20after%20The%20Economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fby-invitation%2F2024%2F05%2F26%2Fai-firms-mustnt-govern-themselves-say-ex-members-of-openais-board%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20op-ed%20by%20former%20OpenAI%20board%20members%20Helen%20Toner%20and%20Tasha%20McCauley%2C%20who%20criticized%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI's%20safety%20practices%20while%20calling%20for%20a%20need%20to%20regulate%20AI.%20The%20title%20of%20the%20piece%20argued%20that%20%26quot%3BAI%20firms%20mustn't%20govern%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20and%20Summers%2C%20the%20two%20current%20members%2C%20pushed%20back%20against%20the%20former%20directors'%20claims%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fby-invitation%2F2024%2F05%2F30%2Fopenai-board-members-respond-to-a-warning-by-former-members%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresponse%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20also%20published%20in%20The%20Economist.%20They%20defended%20Altman%20and%20discussed%20OpenAI's%20stance%20on%20safety%2C%20including%20the%20company's%20formation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sets-up-safety-committee-starts-training-next-frontier-model-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20safety%20committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20set%20of%20voluntary%20commitments%20OpenAI%20made%20to%20the%20White%20House%20to%20reinforce%20safety%20and%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20said%20that%20they%20had%20previously%20chaired%20a%20special%20committee%20as%20part%20of%20the%20newly%20established%20board%20and%20set%20up%20an%20external%20review%20by%20law%20firm%20WilmerHale%20of%20the%20events%20leading%20to%20Altman's%20ousting.%20The%20process%20entailed%20reviewing%2030%2C000%20documents%2C%20along%20with%20dozens%20of%20interviews%20with%20OpenAI's%20previous%20board%2C%20executives%2C%20and%20other%20relevant%20witnesses%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20and%20Summers%20reiterated%20that%20WilmerHale%20concluded%20that%20Altman's%20ousting%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20arise%20out%20of%20concerns%20regarding%20product%20safety%20or%20security%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bthe%20pace%20of%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20op-ed's%20characterization%20that%20Altman%20had%20created%20%26quot%3Ba%20toxic%20culture%20of%20lying%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-member-details-sam-altman-lied-allegation-ousted-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eengaging%20in%20psychologically%20abusive%20behavior%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20the%20two%20current%20board%20members%20said%20they%20had%20found%20Altman%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20forthcoming%20on%20all%20relevant%20issues%20and%20consistently%20collegial%20with%20his%20management%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20published%20the%20same%20day%20as%20her%20op-ed%2C%20Toner%20explained%20why%20the%20former%20board%20previously%20decided%20to%20remove%20Altman%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20lied%20to%20them%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20times%26quot%3B%20and%20withheld%20information.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20the%20old%20OpenAI%20board%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-learned-of-chatgpt-release-on-twitter-helen-toner-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20out%20about%20ChatGPT's%20release%20on%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20perhaps%20difficult%20to%20remember%20now%2C%20Openai%20released%20Chatgpt%20in%20November%202022%20as%20a%20research%20project%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20how%20useful%20its%20models%20are%20in%20conversational%20settings%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20and%20Summers%20wrote%20in%20response.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20built%20on%20gpt-3.5%2C%20an%20existing%20ai%20model%20which%20had%20already%20been%20available%20for%20more%20than%20eight%20months%20at%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToner%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20ahead%20of%20publication.%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20supports%20%26quot%3Beffective%20regulation%20of%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20and%20Altman%2C%20who%20was%20reinstated%20only%20days%20after%20his%20ousting%2C%20has%20%26quot%3Bimplored%26quot%3B%20lawmakers%20to%20regulate%20AI%2C%20the%20two%20current%20board%20directors%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-sam-altman-world-not-far-potentially-scary-ai-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAltman%20has%20been%20advocating%20for%20some%20form%20of%20AI%20regulation%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202015%2C%20more%20recently%20saying%20he%20favors%20the%20formation%20of%20an%20international%20regulating%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he's%20also%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20nervous%20about%20regulatory%20overreach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20World%20Government%20Summit%20in%20February%2C%20Altman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D15UZCAr3shU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esu